div.span: Added: DragonRuby bindings for few libraries!

Cleanup + Improvements for ice_ram.h
1. Cleanup: Removed empty files... 2. ice_ram.h is now compatible with all BSDs in addition to QNX support (So it can work on BlackBerry PlayBook)
Merge branch 'dev' of https://github.com/Rabios/ice_libs into dev

Added some LuaJIT bindings!
Added LuaJIT bindings for following libraries:
1. ice_batt.h 2. ice_clip.h 3. ice_cpu.h 4. ice_ram.h 5. ice_str.h
Edited list of libs required to link in ice_cpu.h
Removed old note about C++ in BlackBerry 10 (Now we use C)

Improvements for ice_cpu.h
1. Now the library is compatible with all BSDs 2. BlackBerry QNX support! (Library now is able to run on BlackBerry PlayBook...) 3. Removed C++ code for BlackBerry 10 implementation (Now BlackBerry 10 support uses same implementation of QNX)

Improvements for ice_str.h
1. Used unsigned long instead of unsigned (This will allow strings to be more wider...) 2. Improved usage of custom memory allocators
No need to include pico_malloc.h and no need to use emmalloc for Web...

3.Improved APIs and added examples for most libraries
[Removed]

Due to Microsoft usage of long long, ice_ram.h switched to C99! :(
